===Etymology===
c.1289, from O.Fr. sucre "sugar" (12c.), from M.L. succarum, from Arabic sukkar, from Pers. shakar, from Skt. sharkara ([[शर्करा]]) "ground or candied sugar," originally "grit, gravel" (cognate with Gk. kroke "pebble").

